name: The Ranch Smokehouse
review_text:
(Translated by Google) We have gone today with our two daughters and chapeau. Spectacular your food and your staff. It shows that the products are of high quality and this together with its good cuisine, makes the meat melt in the mouth, the ribs (ribs), the smoked veal frayed (brisket) and the smoked pork (pork pulled) cinema . The hamburgers have been ordered by my daughters and they are also delightful! The mac'n'cheese, the potatoes and the coleslaw, great.
A 10 for your meal and a 10 for the staff without exception (all who have served us, friendly, fast, with a smile and very professional). With the most contact we have had, a Colombian waiter has given us a brief brushstroke of his adventures in the USA and has advised us in detail of all the dishes. They had not treated us in this way for a long time. Exceptional!
100% recommended, of course we will repeat.

(Original)
Hemos ido hoy con nuestras dos hijas y chapeau. Espectacular su comida y su personal. Se nota que los productos son de alta calidad y esto unido a su buena cocina, hace que la carne se deshaga en la boca, las costillas (ribs), la ternera ahumada deshilachada (brisket) y el cerdo ahumado (pork pulled) de cine. Las hamburguesas las han pedido mis hijas y son también una delicia! Los mac'n'cheese, las patatas y la ensalada de col, buenísimas.
Un 10 para su comida y un 10 para el personal sin excepción (todos los que nos han atendido, amables, rápidos, con una sonrisa y muy profesionales). Con el que mas contacto hemos tenido, un camarero colombiano, nos ha dado una breve pincelada de sus andanzas en USA y nos ha aconsejado detalladamente de todos los platos. Hacía tiempo que no nos habían atendido de esta manera. Excepcional!
Recomendable 100%, por supuesto repetiremos.

name: The Ranch Smokehouse
review_text:
(Translated by Google) Excellent everything. Starting with the attention of Santiago who attended to my girlfriend and me. It is not expensive at all since the quality of the products is far superior. We have eaten a hamburger that they only have for this season and is competing for the best in Spain. We also ordered a combo of 2 meats (Brisket and BBQ ribs) The Brisket very good since it is a cut that is not common but it did not seem extraordinary, instead the ribs were like falls from the sky. The bone came out alone and the meat melts in the mouth. The accompaniments all very special and well made. Freshly made potatoes, Mac and cheese and BBQ beans all very well achieved. Desserts are homemade and made by a boy at home, so support for the local industry is another plus. We ordered a tiramisu that was spectacular. We will surely try all their burgers, meats and desserts. The atmosphere super well achieved and very nice. I congratulate you for the letter, simple and easy to understand. Specialists in their field with a tight letter but all of quality. In short all of 10! Thank you Santiago for such a nice service.

(Original)
Excelente todo. Empezando por la atención de Santiago que fue quien nos atendió a mi novia y a mí. No es para nada caro ya que la calidad de los productos es muy superior. Hemos comido una hamburguesa que solo tienen por esta temporada y está compitiendo por la mejor de España. También pedimos un combo de 2 carnes (Brisket y BBQ ribs) El Brisket muy bueno ya que es un corte que no es común pero no me pareció extraordinario, en cambio las costillas eran como caídas del cielo. El hueso salía solo y la carne se deshace en la boca. Los acompañamientos todos muy especiales y bien hechos. Unas patatas recién hechas, Mac and cheese y judias BBQ todo muy bien logrado. Los postres son caseros y los hace un chico en su casa, así que el apoyo a la industria local es otro plus. Nosotros pedimos un tiramisú que estaba espectacular. Seguro volveremos a probar todas sus hamburguesas, carnes y postres. El ambiente super bien logrado y muy agradable. Los felicito por la carta, sencilla y fácil de entender. Especialistas en su campo con una carta ajustada pero todo de calidad. En resumen todo de 10 ! Gracias Santiago por tan agradable servicio.

El personal es muy amable, eso sí.
owner_answer:
(Translated by Google) Good evening Jordi. Thank you for leaving your most sincere opinion, We would like to recommend that before commenting you could look through our kitchen window to take a look at our DAILY meat smoking process in our Boneless Grills pellet smokers and that our kitchen does not have an oven: ). Besides that our potatoes are hand cut and not frozen.

On the other hand, our average ticket is € 15, which is considered correct. Of course we would like you to give us a second chance.

Regards,
The Ranch Smokehouse Team

(Original)
Buenas noches Jordi. Gracias por dejar tu opinión más sincera, Nos gustaría recomendarte que antes de comentar podías mirar por nuestra ventana a cocina para echar un vistazo a nuestro proceso DIARIO de ahumado de carne en nuestros ahumadores de pellets Boneless Grills y que nuestra cocina no dispone de horno :). Ademas de que nuestras patatas son cortadas a mano y no congeladas.

Por otro lado nuestro ticket medio es de 15€, lo que se considera correcto. Desde luego nos gustaría que nos dieras una segunda oportunidad.

Saludos,
The Ranch Smokehouse Team

A cordial greeting!

The Ranch Smokehouse Team

The Ranch Smokehouse Team

review_text:
(Translated by Google) Given that it is a 'fast food' site, you can't ask for anything better. Smoked meats lots of hours and served with some homemade and incredibly good barbecue sauces. Coleslaw, super fresh, and refillable sodas. They also have vegetarian options (salads and hamburgers). The service is friendly, friendly, and most importantly, fast and efficient. The place is clean and they have recycle bins for table services. The atmosphere is cozy and pleasant, with good and warm lighting, pleasant music and an acceptable volume. The value for money - unbeatable location. A place to return, for sure.

(Original)
Teniendo en cuenta que es un sitio de 'comida rápida', no se puede pedir nada mejor. Carnes ahumadas montones de horas y servidas con unas salsas barbacoa caseras e increíblemente buenas. La ensalada de col, super fresca, y los refrescos rellenables. También tienen opciones vegetarianas (ensaladas y hamburguesas). El servicio es amable, simpático, y lo más importante, rápido y eficiente. El local está limpio y tienen papeleras de reciclaje para los servicios de mesa. El ambiente es acogedor y agradable, con buena y cálida iluminación, la música agradable y a un volumen aceptable. La relación calidad- precio - ubicación inmejorable. Un sitio al que volver, seguro.

name: The Ranch Smokehouse
review_text:
(Translated by Google) AMAZING food, of very poor quality.

[IN RESPONSE TO THE RESTAURANT'S COMMENT]

We were a group of 10 work colleagues. Although they have not commented, everyone thinks we will not return.
Sorry to tell you that I will not give you any more opportunity.
And I'm sorry to be so explicit in the following, but it's how you better define what I felt when eating this menu:
- The lumpy mashed potato looked like a dog vomit.
- The sausage was stale. The Durok pig you were talking about, shouldn't be very healthy, poor.
- Potatoes with a taste of stale oil required horrifying.
- And the ribs, well ... they let themselves eat, to survive.

As for 97% of customers who know how to "appreciate" your food ... I can only say that I am totally proud to remain at that 3% who still have the most demanding palate.

Greetings and luck.

(Original)
Comida ASQUEROSA, de muy mala calidad.

[EN RESPUESTA AL COMENTARIO DEL RESTAURANTE]

Fuimos un grupo de 10 compañeros del trabajo. Aunque ellos no hayan comentado, todos opinan que no volveremos.
Siento deciros que no os daré ninguna oportunidad mas.
Y siento ser tan explicito en lo siguiente, pero es como mejor se define lo que sentí al comer este menú:
- El puré de patata lleno de grumos parecia un vomito de perro.
- La butifarra estaba rancia. El cerdo Durok del que hablais, no debia estar muy sano, pobre.
- Las patatas con un sabor a aceite rancio requemado horroroso.
- Y las costillas, bueno... se dejaban comer, para sobrevivir.

En cuanto al 97% de los clientes que saben "apreciar" vuestra comida... solo puedo decir que estoy totalmemte orgulloso de permanecer a ese 3% que aun tienen el paladar algo mas exigente.

Saludos y suerte.

Hola Jonatan! Lamento tu mala experiencia en nuestro rancho. Nuestra ternera es Black Angus de primera y nuestro cerdo ecológico es Duroc, todo de procedencia local. name: The Ranch Smokehouse
review_text:
I hate to give this one star. Let me explain why. Me and my wife tend to quite strictly go to 4 star or over establishments. At the time we visited this restaurant gets 4.4 stars. Now I've been to a lot of BBQ restaurants from places like Hawksmoor in London to cafe de klos in Amsterdam (highly recommend both of these places). I had high expectations going in.

When we arrived we second guessed going in as it looked and seems to market itself as a chain even though it isn't. It was very quiet inside which perhaps should have served as a warning. We went in regardless on the back of good reviews.

The staff were extremely welcoming and friendly. We were served by a very friendly blonde lady.

So you pick your food at the counter and pay straight away. We picked and I got the beef brisket, ribs, signature fries and Mac and cheese. My wife got one of the veggie burgers. They explained that it only came with one side so she chose fries and then also added BBQ beans. We both ordered soft drinks.

We were presented with non recyclabe cups and we were told to use the refillable machine.

Our food arrived on a mound of paper sheets, boxes and some plastic cutlery. I cannot believe that in 2019 people are being this eco-backwards. My wifes food had an extra portion of chips and when queried we were told that she order extra fries on top of what already came with the burger. We were ok to put that down to the language barrier.

All of our food was cold, except for the Mac and cheese which was actually hot. Bizarrely there was only 1 other table in the whole restaurant with 3 people on and us. I would understand this perhaps happening if it was packed out and the staff were overrun.

I let our server know about this and she took it back and made us new food. When it returned our food was hot but the Mac and cheese was now cold in bits as was the beans kind of like when you microwave something and some bits end up warm and others not so much.

At no point was an apology or any kind of refund offered.

To top it off they dragged a massive bin from the street through the restaurant, past our table and through into the kitchen which seemed like a very strange thing to do while guests were there.

Because our food was served on trays there were also bins (like you find on MC Donalds so you can throw everything left straight in.

A few suggestions to the restaurant:
- It seems like you are trying to be both fast food and also a good sit down restaurant. Pick one or the other.
- Use proper knifes, forks and plates. No one wants to eat ribs with plastic cutlery.
- Also it's 2019. Use glasses. Not plastic cups!
- People should pay at the end of the meal. It isn't ok for there to be poor service/food quality and for the customer to pay full price at the start of the meal.
- you're an American BBQ restaurant but you don't have any whisky on your menu? That's crazy!

I notice offers have mentioned about plastic cutlery etc being used on other comments now that I read in and you seem to have a bit of a generic response about learning from mistakes and you hope the people will come back. Unfortunately unless you change I don't think people will.

The worst thing is, your food isn't too bad (when hot)!

name: The Ranch Smokehouse
review_text:
As an American who hasn't been back home in about a year, I've been dying for some good barbecue. Saw this place while catching a bus, and I have to say that this place is 100% authentic, and some of the best barbecue I've ever had anywhere. Especially the brisket.

Not only that, but they've absolutely nailed the atmosphere. Beautiful hardwood tables and chairs, very comfortable benches, a cool wall of fire in the entrance, and just enough things on the wall- a neon sign or two, a speed limit sign, etc.- but it's not overly kitschy. It's very tastefully done, and comfortable.

I loved the music. Hearing bands like Molly Hatchet and .38 Special, etc. just added to the whole experience. Plus the people working there are super friendly, and the service is excellent.
owner_answer:
Howdy Justin!

We're glad that you enjoyed our food, our service and our ranch. We are in truly love with BBQ world and, after visiting Texas few times, we decided to open this local for sharing the passion of American smoked food with everybody. All of our recipes were created by authentic BBQ chefs like Slappy Yo' Daddy and Moe Cason, so we learnt from the best. We are very happy to read your review and your appreciations of the atmosphere. Hope you can visit your home soon. Y'all come back whenever you want, our doors will always be open for you. :)

name: The Ranch Smokehouse
review_text: We were spending a couple of days in Barcelona and spotted this place whilst travelling on the Hop-on/Hop-off bus. Not being impressed by the local restaurants, and fed up with cheese burgers and fried chicken, we decided to give them a try and were so glad we did. Best meal we had had in days and nice to find somewhere that served 'proper' food. The brisket was amazing and served in a decent sized portion. The staff were so friendly and helpful and we cannot recommend them highly enough. Understand this is a new business and so we wish them every success for the future. If we are ever in Barcelona again, we will definitely go back.

And the hamburger takes about 15 to 20 minutes (notice on the entrance panel). 
The food is good and the potatoes are excellent but the quantity of the supplements is not enough.
A water costs € 2.30, a large salad (simple, without filling the bowl and below hollow) € 6, burger (cheese, caramelized onion and lettuce) € 7.99

(Original)
Para no volver, nada más llegar te encuentras en la pared un gran panel con la carta en su gran mayoría en inglés (si sólo quieren turistas deberían avisarnos antes), un empleado amable nos explica cómo van los platos pero no de manera clara, allí pedimos y el lo apunta en el mantel de papel de la bandeja, de ahí pasamos  por todo un mostrador con comida a la caja dónde tenemos que repetir lo que queremos. Cómo yo me pido una ensalada (a mi gusto) tengo que retroceder hasta dónde están las ensaladas y como hay un cristal le tengo que decir a la cajera que quiero que me ponga, el bol de la ensalada no lo llena y tengo que decir por 3 veces que me eche más lechuga (cada vez que se lo digo me pone 2 hojitas). Pagamos y esperamos en la mesa a que nos traigan la comida. Todos los productos son desechables, con cubiertos de plástico, ideal para el medio ambiente. Y la hamburguesa tardan en hacerla entre 15 y 20 minutos (está advertido en el panel de la entrada).
La comida es buena y las patatas excelentes pero la cantidad de los complementos insuficiente.
Un agua cuesta 2.30€, una ensalada grande (sencilla, sin llenar el bol y por abajo hueco) 6€, hamburguesa (queso, cebolla caramelizada y lechuga) 7.99€
owner_answer:

owner_answer:
(Translated by Google) How you doin ', Ivan? We sincerely feel that your experience on our ranch has not been entirely satisfactory. As we warned in one of our main signs, the wait is due to the type of meat. These are smoked meats in American wood, which need several hours of cooking depending on your choice, so depending on the smoked state they are in, we can prepare it with greater or lesser brevity, but always guaranteeing the quality of the meat . In relation to the letter, you can see in the menu that all the options have a small description in Spanish to explain what it is about, and in the same way our staff is at your complete disposal to explain or help you in everything you need. In the end, there are typical names of American cuisine that we can not translate, such as Pig Candies (fried and caramelized pork dices), but that does not only happen in our restaurant, but in any that offers traditional dishes foreign (as for example the "falafel", which here we call it the same because we do not have a translation into Spanish, the "moussaka", the "coulant" ...). Regarding the price, all our products are Duroc denomination and have the WELFARE seal (the most demanding international standard currently in animal welfare treatment) and PLA production (Certified Antibiotic Free Production), hence the price increase. It is about ecological and local products. We hope to see you soon for a second chance :) Seeya!

(Original)
How you doin', Ivan? Sentimos de corazón que tu experiencia en nuestro rancho no haya resultado del todo satisfactoria. Tal y como avisamos en uno de nuestros carteles principales, la espera se debe a la tipología de la carne. Se trata de carnes ahumadas en madera americana, que necesitan varias horas de cocción dependiendo de tu elección, por lo que según el estado de ahumado en el que se encuentren, podremos preparártela con mayor o menor brevedad, pero siempre garantizando la calidad de la carne. En relación a la carta, puedes observar en el menú que todas las opciones tienen una pequeña descripción en castellano para explicar de qué se trata, y de igual forma nuestro staff está a tu completa disposición para explicarte o ayudarte en todo lo que necesites. Al final, hay nombres típicos de la gastronomía americana que no podemos traducir, como por ejemplo los Pig Candies (dados de carne de cerdo fritos y caramelizados), pero eso no solo pasa en nuestro restaurante, sino en cualquiera que ofrezca platos de cocina tradicional extranjera (como por ejemplo el "falafel", que aquí lo llamamos igual porque no tenemos traducción al castellano, la "moussaka", el "coulant"...). Respecto al precio, todos nuestros productos son denominación Duroc y tienen el sello WELFARE (normativa internacional más exigente actualmente en tratamiento de bienestar animal) y producción PLA (Producción Libre de Antibióticos certificada), de ahí el incremento de precio. Se trata de productos ecológicos y locales. Esperamos verte pronto para una segunda oportunidad :) Seeya!

name: The Ranch Smokehouse
review_text: Place with lot of potential. Though the meat is precooked 10/20 hours and should be excellent, when served the brisket has stayed outside for too long and was dry and pork ribs didn’t came off. Plastic cutlery also downgrades from rib join to fast food. Two weeks open. Place is empty as well. I hope they can make few tweaks and I can call this legendary place after 10 years when visiting Barcelona again.
owner_answer: Howdy Taavi! Thank ya very much for your review. This lets us improve a little every day. We're very sorry for your experience and we hope that if you ever visit Barcelona again, you come back to our ranch for seeing (and tasting!) our improvements. We've learnt from best BBQ chefs in USA like Moe Cason or Slap Yo Daddy BBQ and we don't stop til' we could offer the perfect American BBQ food service. Y'all come back! :)

name: The Ranch Smokehouse
review_text:
(Translated by Google) Today we have found this novelty: The paradise of carnivores. The treatment has been excellent from the owner, the atmosphere is very pleasant (traditional pop music, from Maroon 5 with This Girl to Kiss Me by Sixpence None the Richer) with comfortable sofas.

Upon entering you have the bar with all the gastronomic offer for your enjoyment and enjoyment (do not stop looking at the shiny bacon).

Today we have tried the HAPPY HOUR, from 5 to 7pm ONE QUILO of glazed wings with fries for € 5 + drink. Two people have paid 10 euros almost. They were very good and the spicy BBQ sauce that you find on the table is perfect for potatoes (even wings!).

We will be back, we won't be left without trying the glazed bacon, the very tender brisket and the pulled pork!

Al entrar tienes la barra con toda la oferta gastronómica para tu goce y disfrute (no dejes de mirar al bacon brillante).

Hoy hemos probado la HAPPY HOUR, de 5 a 7pm UN QUILO de alitas glaseadas con patatas fritas por 5€ + bebida. Dos personas hemos pagado 10 euros casi. Estaban muy buenas y la salsa BBQ especiada que encuentras en la mesa es perfecta para las patatas (incluso para las alitas!).

Volveremos, ¡no nos quedaremos sin probar el bacon glaseado, el brisket tiernísimo y el pulled pork!
